request.description:
Execute multiple intents in a single batch request. This is useful for reducing network overhead when you need to perform multiple operations. All intents in the batch are processed atomically - if one fails, all fail. Each intent in the array follows the same structure as individual intent requests.

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "intents": [
    {
      "intent": "record:trajectory",
      "realm": "{{realm}}",
      "payload": {...}
    },
    {
      "intent": "transfer:credits",
      "realm": "{{realm}}",
      "payload": {...}
    }
  ]
}
```

**Best Practices:**
- Keep batch sizes reasonable (recommended: 10-50 intents per batch)
- All intents must belong to the same realm
- Use idempotency keys for critical operations
- Handle partial failures gracefully
